Greetings to Kim Jong Il from Putin 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 9 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il received a message of greetings from Russian President V. Putin Sunday, the 59th anniversary of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The message said that close relations of friendship exist between Russia and the DPRK, expressing the belief that the bilateral good-neighborly relations would make a distinguished contribution to ensuring peace, stability and security in the Korean Peninsula and all other areas of Asia in the future, too. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The message wished Kim Jong Il good health and greater success in his responsible state work and the friendly DPRK peace and prosperity.

Greetings from Chinese Leaders 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 8 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il, Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, and Kim Yong Il, premier of the DPRK Cabinet, received a message of greetings from Hu Jintao, General Secretary of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China, President of the People's Republic of China and chairman of the Central Military Commission of the PRC, Wu Bangguo, chairman of the Standing Committee of the Chinese National People's Congress, and Wen Jiabao, premier of the State Council of China, on Saturday on the occasion of the 59th anniversary of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The message said that the foundation of the DPRK opened a new chapter that enabled the Korean people to become the master of the country and build a socialist state. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the Korean people have achieved great successes in carrying out the cause of socialist construction by displaying the spirit of self-reliance and fortitude under the leadership of President Kim Il Sung, General Secretary Kim Jong Il and the WPK, the message sincerely hoped that the Korean people would achieve steady and fresh success in all work in the future. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is our hope that China will advance alongside the DPRK side and boost cooperation with it in keeping with the times and inject greater dynamism into the traditional Sino-DPRK friendship and thus provide the peoples of the two countries with greater happiness and make fresh contributions to promoting the regional peace and stability, the message added.

Message of Greetings to Kim Jong Il from AINDF 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 9 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il received a message of greetings from the Central Committee of the Anti-Imperialist National Democratic Front on September 9, the 59th anniversary of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The message said that the feats President Kim Il Sung performed by setting forth the Juche-oriented idea of nation-building and laying an eternal foundation for building a great prosperous powerful socialist nation with his outstanding idea and energetic leadership would last forever along with history. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the President's Juche-oriented idea of nation-building and exploits performed in it have been firmly defended by Kim Jong Il and further exalted thanks to the cause of building a great prosperous powerful nation, the message said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK has dynamically advanced along the Juche-oriented road of socialism, preserving its revolutionary character with the whole Party and army and all the people single-mindedly united despite the complicated world-wide political upheavals. It has demonstrated its might to the world, wining only victories in the confrontation with the U.S. imperialists styling themselves the world's "only superpower." This is the precious fruition of your outstanding Songun revolutionary leadership. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 You, the peerless patriot, have ushered in the June 15 era of independent reunification with your patriotic Songun policy, distinguished political ability and immense broad magnanimity and wisely led the struggle to bring about a new turning point for the country's reunification by the concerted efforts of our nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 You are the great elder statesman in the world and distinguished leader of the times as you have remarkably heightened the international position and influence of Songun Korea and led the human cause of independence desirous of sovereignty, independence and socialism to victory by adhering to firm revolutionary and independent principle in the external activities of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The vanguard fighters of the AINDF and patriotic people from all walks of life will eternally glorify the President's idea of nation-building and exploits performed in it and uphold with loyalty your idea and leadership for the country's reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We will achieve the cause of independent reunification through the struggle to implement the tasks of attaching importance to the nation, defending peace and achieving unity in the idea of "By our nation itself" and realize a great alliance against conservatives at an early date and thus resolutely smash the pro-U.S. reactionary forces' attempt to seize power.

National Meeting Marks Anniversary of DPRK 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 8 (KCNA) -- A national meeting was held at the April 25 House of Culture Saturday to mark the 59th anniversary of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the meeting were senior Party, army and state officials, members of the Cabinet, deputies to the Supreme People's Assembly in Pyongyang, officials of the Party, armed forces and power organs, social organizations, ministries and national institutions and working people in Pyongyang, overseas Koreans including members of the congratulatory group of Koreans in Japan and the chief of the Pyongyang mission of the Anti-Imperialist National Democratic Front. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there on invitation were diplomatic envoys of different countries, representatives of international organizations and officials of different embassies here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Yong Il, premier of the Cabinet, in a report said that the foundation of the DPRK was a shining victory of the Juche-oriented line of nation- building advanced by President Kim Il Sung and marked a historic event as it brought about a fundamental turn in carving out the destiny of the Korean nation and accomplishing the revolutionary cause of Juche. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After the founding of the DPRK it emerged on the international arena as a full-fledged independent and sovereign state although Korea suffered an eclipse on the world map in the past. It was a genuine model in building a socialist state in the human political history, thus positively encouraging the world revolutionary people in their struggle for national and class emancipation and the independence of the popular masses, the reporter said, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A steady continuity is given to the glorious history of the DPRK thanks to Kim Jong Il and the DPRK is dynamically advancing toward the bright future of a great prosperous powerful country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK has self-reliant national defence capability strong enough to beat back any formidable enemy at a single stroke and is demonstrating its might as an invincible military power while energetically pushing forward the building of a great prosperous powerful socialist country, meeting all challenges of the imperialists. This is the most spectacular success made by the army and people of the DPRK in consolidating it under the Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il of which they feel highly proud. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporter called for holding Kim Il Sung in high esteem as the eternal President of the DPRK and founder of socialist Korea in all ages and carrying on the revolutionary struggle and construction as intended by him under any circumstances and thus making the country always shine as the glorious country of Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He underlined the need to eternally glorify the Songun revolutionary history of Kim Jong Il, who has brought about the great heyday of the country with his great Songun leadership, as an eternal cornerstone of the DPRK and the most precious national treasure and more thoroughly implement the Workers' Party of Korea's Songun idea and line in all fields of the revolution and construction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He underscored the need to dynamically wage a nationwide struggle for attaching importance to the nation, defending peace and achieving unity on the basis of the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration and the spirit of "By our nation itself" and thus achieve the historic cause of national reunification without fail. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He stated that the army and people of the DPRK vehemently denounce the reckless moves of the U.S. and the Japanese reactionaries, its ally, and will mercilessly punish those who dare try to infringe upon the sovereignty and interests of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK government will stand against the imperialists' moves for domination, interference and war and strive to achieve stability and progress in Asia and the rest of the world in unity with the peoples of all countries advocating independence in the idea of independence, peace and friendship, he concluded.

Homage Paid to President Kim Il Sung 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 9 (KCNA) -- Senior party and state officials, chairman of a friendly party, Cabinet members, deputies to the Supreme People's Assembly in Pyongyang and leading officials of party and power organs, public organizations, ministries and national institutions visited the Kumsusan Memorial Palace Sunday to pay homage to President Kim Il Sung on the occasion of the 59th birthday of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Placed before the statue of the President was a floral basket in the joint name of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, the WPK Central Military Commission, the DPRK National Defence Commission, the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly and the DPRK Cabinet. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Written on the ribbon of the floral basket were letters reading "The great leader Comrade Kim Il Sung is immortal." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants paid high tribute to the statue. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They made a bow in humble reverence to the President who built the socialist state centering around the popular masses and demonstrated its dignity and might to the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Anti-Japanese revolutionary fighters, servicepersons, officials of organs of different levels and people from all walks of life also visited the memorial palace on the same day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Visitors to the memorial palace today included the diplomatic corps and the military attaches' corps here, the congratulatory group of Koreans in Japan celebrating the 59th founding anniversary of the DPRK, a delegation of the China Association for International Friendly Contact, a Qatar delegation of Al-Jazeera Satellite Television and overseas compatriots and foreign guests.

Floral Baskets Laid before Statues of Kim Il Sung 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 9 (KCNA) -- Baskets of flowers were placed before the statues of President Kim Il Sung on the occasion of the 59th birthday of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Seen standing before the statue of Kim Il Sung on Mansu Hill was a floral basket from General Secretary Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Laid before the statue were floral baskets in the name of party, military and power organs, social bodies, ministries and national institutions, scientific, educational, cultural and arts, public health and media institutions, industrial establishments, farms and schools, etc. and bouquets and flowers.  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also placed there was a floral basket in the name of the Pyongyang mission of the Anti-Imperialist National Democratic Front. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Written on the ribbons of the floral baskets were such letters as "The great leader Comrade Kim Il Sung will live forever," "The great leader Comrade Kim Il Sung will always be with us" and others. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 People from all walks of life and school youth and children paid high tribute to the statue of the President in humble reverence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, floral baskets were placed before his statues in different parts of the city, including Kim Il Sung University, Kim Il Sung Military University, the Ministry of People's Security, the Korean Film Studio and the Pyongyang Schoolchildren's Palace. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 People and school youth and children across the country laid baskets of flowers, bouquets and flowers before the statues of the President in their residential areas.

Floral Tribute Paid on National Day 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 9 (KCNA) -- Wreaths were laid at the Revolutionary Martyrs Cemetery on Mt. Taesong and the Patriotic Martyrs Cemetery and floral baskets before the Monument to Victory in the Fatherland Liberation War Sunday on the occasion of the 59th founding anniversary of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Seen on the wreath-laying stands of the cemeteries were wreaths sent by General Secretary Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present on the occasion were Kim Yong Nam, Kim Yong Il, Kim Yong Chun, Ri Yong Mu, Kim Il Chol, Choe Thae Bok, Yang Hyong Sop, Kim Ki Nam and Choe Yong Rim, officials of Party, armed forces and power organs, working people's organizations, ministries and national institutions, servicepersons of the Korean People's Army and working people in the city. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Wreaths were placed on the wreath-laying stands of the cemeteries in the name of the Workers' Party of Korea Central Committee, the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly and the DPRK Cabinet and a floral basket was laid in front of the sculpture "Victory," the main theme of the above-said monument, in the joint name of the Central Committee and the Central Military Commission of the WPK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also placed before the cemeteries and the monument were wreaths, floral baskets and bouquets in the name of the Ministry of the People's Armed Forces, working people's organizations, ministries, national institutions, KPA units, institutions of science, education, public health and media and the party and power organs, factories and farms in the city. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants paid high tribute to the revolutionary martyrs who devoted themselves to the country and the revolution, the victory of socialism and the country's prosperity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, wreaths were laid before statues of martyrs, monuments to fallen fighters of the KPA and graves of martyrs across the country.

Homage Paid to Kim Il Sung by Commanding Officers of KPA 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 9 (KCNA) -- Commanding officers of the Korean People's Army visited the Kumsusan Memorial Palace Sunday, the 59th anniversary of the foundation of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They paid high tribute to the statue of President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They made a bow in humble reverence to the President who built the independent socialist state centred on the popular masses and consolidated it into a great bulwark of revolution with his unique idea of nation-building and Songun revolutionary leadership.

Banquet Given to Celebrate DPRK Birthday
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 9 (KCNA) -- The DPRK government gave a banquet at the People's Palace of Culture on Sunday evening on the occasion of the 59th anniversary of the foundation of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were senior Party, army and state officials, chairman of a friendly party, leading officials of party, armed forces and power organs, public organizations, ministries and national institutions, anti-Japanese revolutionary fighters, former unconverted long-term prisoners who are pro-reunification patriotic fighters, officials in the fields of science, education, culture and arts, public health and the press, heroes, men of merits, members of the congratulatory group of Koreans in Japan, overseas Koreans and the chief of the Pyongyang mission of the Anti-Imperialist National Democratic Front. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present on invitation were diplomatic envoys of various countries and staff members of foreign embassies and representatives of international organizations here and foreign guests. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, made a speech at the banquet. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He in his speech said that the whole historic course covered by the DPRK is a glorious history in which it has been developed into a strong socialist power and invincible Songun Korea, overcoming all ordeals and difficulties of history. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that today the DPRK is dynamically advancing toward the bright future of prosperity thanks to the ever-victorious Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il, he said that all the servicepersons and people would share their destiny with the DPRK forever and more dynamically struggle for the building of a great prosperous powerful socialist nation, the independent reunification of the country and the final victory of the revolutionary cause of Juche. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK government will wage a nationwide powerful struggle for attaching importance to the nation, defending peace and achieving unity in the spirit of the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration and in the spirit of "By our nation itself" and thus smash the moves of the separatists at home and abroad and achieve the historic cause of national reunification without fail, he stated, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK government will unite with the peoples of all countries defending independence in the idea of independence, peace and friendship to oppose and reject the imperialists' moves for domination, intervention and war and make positive efforts for stability and development in Asia and the rest of the world.

Egyptian Ambassador Gives Reception 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 8 (KCNA) -- Moustafa Mohamed Ahmed Al Hatter, Egyptian ambassador to the DPRK, hosted a reception at the embassy here on September 7 on the occasion of the 59th founding anniversary of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there on invitation were Vice-President of the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly Kim Yong Dae, Minister of Education Kim Yong Jin, Acting Chairman of the Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries Mun Jae Chol and officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Egyptian ambassador in his speech said the traditional relations of friendship between the two countries provided by President Kim Il Sung and Egyptian leaders are now growing stronger under the deep care of Kim Jong Il and Egyptian President Muhammad Hosni Mubarak. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Referring to the brisk exchange and cooperation between Egypt and the DPRK, he wished the Korean people greater progress and prosperity under the wise leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Yong Dae in his speech said the DPRK is pleased with the fact that the Egyptian leadership and people have set store by the tradition of friendship and extended invariable support and solidarity to the just cause of the Korean people. The DPRK will make positive efforts to boost in all fields the bilateral relations in the future, too, in keeping with the common desire and interests of the two peoples, he stressed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He hoped that the Egyptian government and people would achieve greater success in the work for the development of the country, Arab unity and a fair and comprehensive settlement of the Mideast issue under the leadership of President Muhammad Hosni Mubarak.

Reception Given to Celebrate Birthday of DPRK in China 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Beijing, September 7 (KCNA) -- A reception was given at the DPRK embassy in Beijing on September 7 on the occasion of the 59th birthday of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the reception on invitation were Gu Xiulian, vice-chairwoman of the Standing Committee of the Chinese National People's Congress, Wu Dawei, vice-minister of Foreign Affairs, officials of the International Liaison Department of the C.C., the Communist Party of China, the People's Daily, the Xinhua News Agency, the General Political Department of the Chinese People's Liberation Army and other officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were the DPRK ambassador to China and embassy officials. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Gu Xiulian said at the reception that the founding of the DPRK 59 years ago made it possible for the Korean people to emerge a master of the country and begin building socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Today the Korean people have achieved steady successes in various fields including the economic construction, inter-Korean ties and external relations, united close behind the Workers' Party of Korea headed by General Secretary Kim Jong Il, said Gu Xiulian. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the Sino-DPRK friendship provided by the leaders of the elder generation of the two countries is growing stronger as the years go by and rooted deep in the minds of the two peoples, Gu Xiulian added that the friendship is further developing under the care and leadership of the top leaders of the two countries in the new historical period. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Saying that it is the steadfast policy of the Party and government of China to steadily consolidate and develop the Sino-DPRK friendly and cooperative ties, Gu Xiulian expressed the will to more dynamically boost the traditional Sino-DPRK friendship with the Korean comrades to promote the well-being of the two peoples.

Message of Sympathy to Algerian President 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 8 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, Saturday sent a message of sympathy to Algerian President Abdelaziz Bouteflika in connection with the suicide bombing attack in Algeria that claimed dozens of casualties. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the message Kim extended deep sympathy and condolences to the Algerian president and, through him, to the victims and the bereaved families and reiterated the firm support and solidarity of the DPRK with the national reconciliation policy of the Algerian president and government for stability and unity of the country.

Foreign Delegations Arrive
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 8 (KCNA) -- A delegation of the China Association for International Friendly Contact led by Vice-President Shen Weiping arrived here today by air to mark the 59th anniversary of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On the same day a Qatar delegation of Al-Jazeera Satellite Television led by its Director General Wadah Khanfar came here.

Birthday of DPRK Celebrated in Cuba 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 9 (KCNA) --A Korean book, photo and handicraft exhibition was opened in Old Havana on September 5 with due ceremony on the occasion of the 59th anniversary of the founding of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On display in the venue of the exhibition were famous works of President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il, photos showing their undying feats and books and photos introducing the glorious history of the DPRK and handicrafts reflecting the wisdom and skills of the Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the opening ceremony were officials of the Cuban Foreign Ministry, the Institute of Friendship with the Peoples, the Ministry of Foreign Investment and Economic Cooperation, the Association of the Revolutionary Combatants, the Asian Museum, the Cuban Committee for Supporting Korea's Reunification and Cuba-DPRK Friendship School and the Organization of Solidarity of the Peoples of Africa, Asia and Latin America, people from all walks of life and diplomatic envoys of various countries in Havana. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Juan Jose Leon Vega, chairman of the Cuban Committee for Supporting Korea's Reunification, in a speech at the opening ceremony praised the undying feats performed by the President in founding the DPRK and expressed conviction that the Korean people would bravely overcome all difficulties before them including the natural disasters under the leadership of Kim Jong Il.

Papers Editorially Observe Birthday of DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 9 (KCNA) -- Papers here today dedicate editorials to the 59th anniversary of the foundation of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The foundation of the DPRK by President Kim Il Sung on September 9, Juche 37 (1948) was a historic event that opened up a new era of building a socialist state centered on the popular masses and a great auspicious event that brought about a radical turn in carving out the destiny of the Korean nation, Rodong Sinmun says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The President is a distinguished politician and peerless patriot who built the most dignified and prosperous socialist power of Juche in this land with his clairvoyant wisdom and energetic leadership. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The President, who founded and led the DPRK, was the only state leader who put the dignity and position of the country on a high level and performed such great exploits before the nation in his generation and the Korean people are the only people who inherited the great revolutionary heritage for the country's prosperity from their leader.  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Our socialist country is a precious crystal of the President's idea of believing in the people as in Heaven and his leadership and the DPRK is the state of the President which can go only by his august name. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Today the DPRK is winning victory after victory and prospering on the basis of the Songun revolutionary leadership exploits of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK is a great country prospering thanks to the independent politics of Kim Jong Il and an impregnable socialist power prospering thanks to the military power built by him under the banner of Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is also a promising country in which the whole Party and army and all the people are united around him single-mindedly, the glorious country of Kim Il Sung shining with the august name of the President, the founder of socialist Korea, and a country prospering with his idea and feats as an eternal foundation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK will dynamically advance along the road of victory and glory under the banner of Songun in the future, too. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Minju Joson says the nearly 60 year-long history covered by the DPRK along the road of Songun proves that no force on earth can block the path before all the servicepersons and people holding in high esteem and following the President and Kim Jong Il forever. Very bright is the prospect of the DPRK which has greeted the dawn of a great prosperous powerful nation, the paper notes.

Gift to Kim Jong Il from Chinese Delegation
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 9 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il was presented with a gift by the delegation of the China Association for International Friendly Contact on a visit to the DPRK on the occasion of the 59th birthday of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was handed to an official concerned by its Vice-President Shen Weiping who is leading the delegation.

Dancing Parties of Youth and Students Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 9 (KCNA) -- Dancing parties of youth and students for celebrating the 59th anniversary of the DPRK took place in Pyongyang, Phyongsong, Sariwon, Kanggye, Hamhung, Chongjin and other provincial, city and county seats Sunday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Plazas of the capital city including the Tower of the Juche Idea, the Monument to Party Foundation and the Arch of Triumph and other venues of the events were crowded with youth and students who presented dances representing the boundless longing for President Kim Il Sung who turned Korea which suffered an eclipse on the world map in the past into a socialist power centred on the popular masses and the ardent reverence for Kim Jong Il who is exalting the dignity and might of the country and the nation to the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Youth and students danced to the tune of "Song of the Proclamation of People's Republic", "May the Three Color Flag of the Republic Flutter", "Pyongyang Is Best", "Pride of Youth", "May the Country and Youth Shine" and other songs, increasing the festivity of the jubilee. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@The dancing parties held in different parts of the country fully represented the revolutionary enthusiasm of the young vanguard to fully display the resourcefulness and vigor of the Songun young vanguard in the present worthwhile struggle to build a great prosperous powerful socialist nation under the Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il, holding Kim Il Sung in high esteem as the eternal President of the DPRK.

Kim Jong Il's Work Published in Bangladesh 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 8 (KCNA) -- The famous work of Kim Jong Il "Socialism Is a Science" was brought out in pamphlet by the Bangladesh-Korea Friendship and Solidarity Committee on September 2. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The work, published on November 1, Juche 83 (1994) clarifies the fact that Korean-style socialism based on the Juche-oriented socialist theory is the most scientific and vital socialism and principled issues arising in defending socialism.

DPRK's National Day Celebrated 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 8 (KCNA) -- Seminars, round-table talks, photo exhibitions and film shows were held in Mexico, Romania and Malaysia on August 28 and 29 on the occasion of the 59th founding anniversary of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On display in the venues of the events were photos showing the undying exploits President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il performed by founding the DPRK and strengthening it and photos introducing Songun Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants of the film shows watched Korean films including "For the Liberation of the Country" and "The Rivers and Mountains of the Country Taking on More Beautiful Looks under the Leadership of the Great General."

Information Bulletin Issued to Mark Birthday of DPRK in Mexico 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 8 (KCNA) -- The Mexican Committee for the Study of Kimilsungism issued information bulletin titled "The country advancing under the banner of Songun" on the occasion of the 59th anniversary of the foundation of the DPRK. It carried a photo of President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il standing together. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The bulletin said that the history of the DPRK demonstrating its dignity as a "small yet great country" in the international community would have been unthinkable without Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the DPRK is demonstrating its increasing might thanks to Songun, the bulletin stressed that the ceaseless field guidance provided by Kim Jong Il helped the Korean People's Army grow stronger politically and militarily and emerge an army capable of beating back any formidable enemy at a single stroke. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Songun policy has resulted in rapidly expanding and developing the external relations of the DPRK and bringing about a landmark turn in the process of the reunification of the Korean Peninsula, the bulletin noted, adding that the DPRK will always emerge victorious under the banner of Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also edited in the bulletin are the emblem and flag of the DPRK and a photo introducing Songun Korea.

DPRK's Birthday Observed in China 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Beijing, September 6 (KCNA) -- The Chinese People's Association for Friendship with Foreign Countries and the China-Korea Friendship Association arranged a reception in Beijing on September 6 on the occasion of the 59th anniversary of the founding of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there on invitation were the ambassador and staff members of the DPRK embassy in Beijing. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The vice-president of the Chinese People's Association for Friendship with Foreign Countries in a speech at the reception noted that the Korean people have achieved noticeable successes through an indomitable struggle to defend and build the country in the spirit of sovereignty and independence and fortitude under the leadership of President Kim Il Sung and the Workers' Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He noted that the Korean people are now striving hard to build a great prosperous powerful nation, united close around the WPK headed by General Secretary Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Pointing out that the traditional friendship provided and developed by the leaders of the elder generation of the two countries has been deeply rooted in the minds of the people of the two countries, he said that the frequent mutual visits of the top leaders in recent years helped further promote the understanding and friendship between the two countries and the two peoples. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the steadfast policy of the party and government of China and the earnest desire of the Chinese people to consolidate the traditional Sino-Korean friendship, he said, stressing that China would as ever make strenuous efforts together with the Korean comrades to develop the Sino-Korean friendship generation after generation.

Reception Given at DPRK Embassy in Moscow 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Moscow, September 6 (KCNA) -- A reception was given at the DPRK embassy in Moscow on September 5 on the occasion of the 59th anniversary of the founding of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the reception on invitation were a deputy speaker of the Russian State Duma and other officials of the government, political parties and organizations and figures in the fields of science, education, culture and arts and media. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Prior to the reception, its participants laid a floral basket and bunches of flowers before the full-length picture of President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then they looked round famous works of the President and Kim Jong Il and photos showing the victorious and glorious history of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Saltanov, vice-minister of Foreign Affairs of Russia, in his speech at the reception offered warm congratulations on the 59th anniversary of the founding of the DPRK, referring to the fact that the two countries have firmly preserved the desire to boost the friendship, good-neighborliness and trust ties in the last period. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Expressing support to the efforts of the DPRK to develop the inter-Korean relations, he hoped that the DPRK would achieve peace and prosperity and Russia-DPRK relations of friendship and good-neighborliness would grow stronger.

National Scientific and Technological Seminar Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 8 (KCNA) -- A national scientific and technological seminar in the field of conserving woodland, plants and land was held at the People's Palace of Culture Friday 60 years after President Kim Il Sung made public his famous work "Let Us Launch a Vigorous Tree Planting Movement Involving All the Masses" and 50 years after Kim Jong Il planted trees on Mt. Jang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An Pyong So, vice-chairman of the Central Committee of the DPRK Natural Conservation Union, in his speech at the seminar said that the President set forth an important task to be fulfilled to create woodland through a mass movement in the historical talk he had with officials on Munsu Hill after the liberation of the country. The speaker stressed that the work serves as guidelines, a militant banner to be held fast to in turning the country into a picturesque land of bliss for the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He recalled that Kim Jong Il climbed Mt. Jang in spring of Juche 46 (1957) and planted trees, urging students to plant even one more tree and take good care of it for the future of the country and instilling ardent patriotism into them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Presented at the seminar were at least 20 papers on the new scientific and technological results and experience of practical value gained by officials, scientists, technicians and experts in the field of conserving woodland, plants and land across the country. They include papers titled "The technological problem in more rapidly propagating many more trees of good species" and "Research into technological method to promote the afforestation." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Introduced there were achievements made in researches into the peculiarities of growth and propagation of plants, the method of administering land in order to increase the fertility of soil for double-cropping, taking measures to conserve land in designing man-made grass fields and others.

Abolition of NSL Demanded in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 8 (KCNA) -- The south Korean People's Solidarity for the Abolition of the "National Security Law" reportedly held a press conference in Seoul on September 3 in which it demanded the immediate presentation of the "bill on the abolition of the NSL" to the "National Assembly" and the passage of it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The speakers at the conference noted that it is a historical task the implementation of which brooks no further delay to scrap all the evil laws including the NSL and eradicate the leftovers of the Cold War era. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A press release read out at the conference said that the peace-keeping mechanism on the Korean Peninsula can never go together with the NSL, holding that the NSL should be abolished at once at the regular session of the "National Assembly" as it goes against peace and reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It warned that if the Grand National Party of south Korea again strongly opposes the carriage of the above-said bill, it will not be able to escape a stern judgment of history, to say nothing of the disbandment of the party itself. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An action program of the campaign for the abolition of the NSL in the latter half of 2007 was announced at the conference.

National Seminar in Fields of Education and Science Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Hamhung, September 7 (KCNA) -- A national seminar in fields of education and science took place in Hamhung on September 6 and 7 on the occasion of the 60th anniversary of the foundation of Hamhung University of Chemical Engineering. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The seminar was divided into a seminar on teaching methods and a seminar on science. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Presented at the seminar on teaching methods were at least 120 papers from nine panels including socio-politics, basic education and electronics and information. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The papers attracted attention of the participants as they dealt with the experience in fostering the creative ability of students to put what they have learned into practice, the method of using computer-added visual aids for teaching and the success made in increasing the effectiveness of teaching by use of multimedia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The seminar on science involved 11 panel discussions including light industry, chemical engineering, construction and building-materials and electronic automation. At least 800 papers were presented at the seminar. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants in the seminars exchanged the successes and experience gained in science and education to bring the nation's science and technology to the cutting-edge level, train many scientific and technological talents and place the national economy on a Juche-oriented, modern and scientific basis.

Withdrawal of U.S. Forces from S. Korea Urged
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 8 (KCNA) -- The history of the U.S. imperialists' occupation of south Korea is a history of aggression and crime as they have violated the sovereignty of the Korean nation, wrecked peace and blocked the reunification of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun Saturday says this in a signed article as regards the lapse of 62 years since the U.S. military occupation of south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialist aggression forces in south Korea are as good as a time bomb gravely threatening the peace on the Korean Peninsula and the destiny of the Korean nation and a heavy bar lying in the way of improvement of inter-Korean relations and national reunification, the article notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. occupied south Korea by force of arms and established its colonial domination system there. On the basis of it, it has maliciously blocked the Korean nation's struggle for peace of the country and its reunification while intensifying the moves for aggression on the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. policy of occupying south Korea is chiefly aimed at invading the DPRK and realizing its ambition for military domination over the whole of the Korean Peninsula which is situated in a strategically important position. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists ignited the Korean war in 1950, fully revealing before the world the aggressive nature of their occupation of south Korea and their true colors as a criminal. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Even after the end of the Cold War the U.S. has not discarded its anachronistic Korea policy but continued resorting to arms buildup and anti-DPRK war exercises in south Korea, thus rendering the situation on the Korean Peninsula to the extreme pitch of tension and increasing the danger of outbreak of a nuclear war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. advertises that its military presence in south Korea is to "deter someone's provocation" and "keep peace" in and around the Korean Peninsula. But it is sheer sophism confusing the right and wrong and a crafty deception to justify and perpetuate the U.S. imperialist aggression forces' occupation of south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Their occupation of south Korea can never be justified. With nothing can the U.S. conceal the crime-woven history of 62 years during which it has wantonly violated the dignity and sovereignty of the Korean nation, gravely wrecked peace of the Korean Peninsula and sought the confrontation between the north and the south and their permanent division after occupying south Korea by force of arms. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There is no justification and pretext for the U.S. to keep its aggression forces in south Korea.

Early Withdrawal of U.S. Forces Called for
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 8 (KCNA) -- The U.S. Forces Command in south Korea is stepping up the restructuring of its armed forces and staging war exercises against the DPRK almost everyday, while blustering recently that it would "turn its forces into a more powerful army to deter provocations" after listing the DPRK as a "country to blame for those provocations." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun Saturday observes in a signed article in this regard: The U.S. moves to permanently keep its aggression forces in south Korea can never be pardoned as they are anachronistic and perfidious acts to threaten the peace and security of the Korean Peninsula and block the independent and peaceful reunification of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. continued military presence in south Korea is quite contrary to the trend of the present times toward independence, peace and reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is as clear as noonday that durable peace can neither settle on the Korean Peninsula nor can the June 15 era of reunification make smooth progress as long as the U.S. imperialist aggression forces are present in south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They professed to be "liberator" and "friend" from the outset of their occupation of south Korea but could not conceal their true colors as an aggressor, plunderer and murderer. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They plundered south Korean peasants of a large area of farm land, their means of living, turning it into the U.S. military bases. And they are forcing south Korea to spend money exceeding 3 billion U.S. dollars collected from south Koreans as taxes as "funds for the upkeep of U.S. forces." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Koreans will never allow the U.S. to perpetuate its forces' presence in south Korea but wage a persistent struggle to drive the aggressors out of south Korea at any cost.

5th National Show of Korean Dresses Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 8 (KCNA) -- The 5th national show of Korean dresses took place here from September 4 to 7 under the sponsorship of the Association of Korean Dress-makers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Displayed in the venue were at least 800 suits of Korean dresses presented by ministries, national institutions, public service establishments from across the country and members of the Korean Democratic Women's Union. The show was divided into everyday dresses, holiday clothes and children's clothes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Attracting the attention of visitors were Korean jackets made of bright and gentle silk including Korean white silk jackets and three or two-color jackets. Everyday dresses good and convenient for activities presented by members of the women's union in various parts of the country, in particular, fully represented the zeal of the Korean women to preserve the excellent tradition of Korean dresses and further develop it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 While the show was under way it involved diverse programs such as fashion show, lectures on how to design and make Korean dresses and technical service.

Kim Il Sung's Immortal Feats in Building of Socialist State 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 8 (KCNA) -- The Korean people with deep emotion are looking back on the immortal feats performed by President Kim Il Sung in creating a new history of building a socialist state on the occasion of the 59th anniversary of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 With a scientific penetration into the requirement of the times and revolutionary development in his early revolutionary activities, the President organized and led the great anti-Japanese war under the banner of Juche idea and energetically pushed ahead with the preparatory work for establishing a genuine revolutionary power. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He put forward the line on building a new form of government at the Kalun Meeting and clarified the task to overturn the ruling system of the brigandish Japanese imperialists and set up a genuine people's government by realizing a broad national united front in the "Ten-point Programme of the Association for the Restoration of the Fatherland." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In particular, the people's revolutionary governments established in the guerrilla bases under the leadership of the President were the historical root for the foundation and development of the DPRK, which was the origin of the people-centered new state building. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Based on the experience of the anti-Japanese armed struggle, he wisely led the struggle for accomplishing the cause of founding the DPRK after the liberation of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The obstructions of the U.S. imperialists and the traitors to the nation at that time brought manifold obstacles and difficulties to the efforts to establish a unified democratic central government and an independent and sovereign state for which the people had longed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Under such situation, the President set up the central power organ to guide the already formed local people's government bodies in north Korea in a unified way and consolidated the material foundation for building an independent and sovereign state. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 When the U.S. imperialists and its stooges unscrupulously rigged up the "separate election and separate government" in south Korea, he put forward the policy of setting up a supreme legislative body representing the whole of Korea and enforcing the constitution of the DPRK and roused the working masses to the struggle for founding the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His energetic guidance resulted in the foundation of the DPRK on September 9, Juche 37 (1948) at last and he was elected the head of the state in accordance with the unanimous desire and will of the entire Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Today the Korean people, with Kim Il Sung as the eternal President of the DPRK, are creditably carrying his plan for building a rich and strong nation into practice under the Songun revolutionary leadership of Kim Jong Il.

Russian Dance Company Gives Its Premiere 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 8 (KCNA) -- The visiting State Academic Moiseyev Dance Company of Russia gave its premiere at the East Pyongyang Grand Theatre Saturday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Russian artistes impressively represented the heroism displayed by the Russian people in the battles during the just Patriotic War and the militant and optimistic life of seamen with perfect ensemble, refined dancing skill and dynamic rhythms. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They successfully presented a Moldovan humor dance "Tabakeryaska", a Uzbek dance "Dish Dance", a Chinese ribbon dance, a Venezuelan dance "Joropo" and other folk dances of various countries and nations to suit the thematic contents of the numbers, winning the acclaim of the audience. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They also put on the stage a Korean dance "Trio Dance".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performance was appreciated by servicepersons.

Art Performance Given to Celebrate 59th National Day
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 8 (KCNA) -- A music and dance performance celebrating the 59th founding anniversary of the DPRK was given at the Ponghwa Art Theatre today. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Artistes of the Mansudae Art Troupe raised the curtain with mixed duet and chorus "Song Devoted to Marshal Kim Il Sung." Their repertoire included colorful numbers in which they sang high praises of the undying exploits President Kim Il Sung performed by founding the people's republic and building a socialist power, independent in politics, self-supporting in economy and self-reliant in national defence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performance made a successful artistic representation of the firm faith of the Korean people that the country will always remain shining as Korea of President Kim Il Sung under the Songun revolutionary leadership of Kim Jong Il, the destiny of the country and the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performance was appreciated by senior officials of the party, the army and the state, chairman of friendly party, members of the Cabinet, deputies to the Supreme People's Assembly in Pyongyang, officials of the armed forces organs, power bodies, public organizations, ministries and national institutions, servicepersons of the Korean People's Army, officials in the fields of science, education, culture and arts, public health and media, persons of merit and working people in Pyongyang, overseas Koreans including the congratulatory group of Koreans in Japan and the chief of the Pyongyang Mission of the Anti-Imperialist National Democratic Front. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present to appreciate the performance on invitation were diplomatic envoys and staff members of embassies of various countries and representatives of international organizations here and other foreign guests.

DPRK's National Day Observed in Foreign Countries
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 9 (KCNA) -- Lectures were given in Democratic Congo, South Africa, Tanzania and India from August 29 to September 2 on the occasion of the 59th founding anniversary of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Otete Gaston Mboyo, chairman of the National Committee of the Genuine Lumumbist Patriotic Party of Democratic Congo, in a lecture said that the DPRK is called Kim Il Sung's Korea because the exploits he performed by building the DPRK and developing it are great and immortal. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Bonakele Majuba, secretary of the Mfumalanga Provincial Committee of the South African Communist Party and chairman of the South African Association of Friendship and Solidarity with Korean People, said the DPRK founded by President Kim Il Sung is the society where the Juche idea that man is the master of everything and decides everything is embodied and all the people lead a harmonious and happy life, enjoying such benefits as free medical care and universal free and compulsory education and a strong socialist bulwark guaranteed by the Songun idea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 R.W.W. Kente, secretary general of the Tanzanian National Coordinating Committee of the Juche Idea Study Groups, said the might of the DPRK has been further augmented thanks to the Songun politics of Kim Jong Il and under his wise leadership the Korean people are defending socialism and carving out a new era of building a great prosperous powerful nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The secretary general of the Indian Youth Group for the Study of Works of Comrade Kim Il Sung stressed that the DPRK is an impregnable fortress defending people's destiny with strong military power and a cradle of happiness guaranteeing the people a sound and highly civilized material and cultural life.

Birthday of DPRK Observed in Japan
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Tokyo, September 7 (KNS-KCNA) -- A reception was given at the Korean Hall in Tokyo on September 7 on the occasion of the 59th birthday of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the reception were officials of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon) and Korean businessmen.  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present on invitation were figures of political, economic, press, public and cultural circles of Japan, ambassadors of various countries to Japan and staff members of different embassies and representatives of international bodies in Japan and Yun Kil Sang, chairman of the Federation of Koreans in the U.S. on a visit to Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 So Man Sul, chairman of the Central Standing Committee of Chongryon, said that the DPRK was recently hard hit by torrential rain-induced flood but all the people are energetically coming out in unity to clear away the flood damage as early as possible under the wise leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He urged the Japanese authorities to immediately lift sanctions against the DPRK imposed upon it as part of their hostile policy toward it and Koreans in Japan, halt their reckless suppression of Chongryon and sincerely opt for normalizing the DPRK-Japan relations on the basis of Japan's settlement of its past wrongs in the basic spirit of the DPRK-Japan Pyongyang Declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On the same day, a lecture took place at the Korean Hall in Tokyo on the same occasion under the sponsorship of the Chongryon Central Standing Committee.

Congratulatory Letter to Kim Jong Il from Chongryon
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 9 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il received a congratulatory letter from the Central Standing Committee of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon) on September 9, the 59th anniversary of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The letter said that the immortal exploits President Kim Il Sung performed by providing a genuine cradle of life which guarantees the Korean people eternal happiness with his unique idea and theory on building an independent and sovereign state and distinguished leadership will always last along with the history of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Juche Korea has decisively overpowered the formidable enemy while demonstrating its might as an invincible power, defended its independent dignity of the country and the nation advancing along the orbit of Juche and shed brilliant rays all over the world as the bulwark of socialism powerfully propelling the human cause of independence as it is led by you the peerless brilliant Songun commander who rose as the sun of the nation carrying forward the spirit of Mt. Paektu, the letter noted, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The officials of Chongryon and Koreans in Japan have dynamically advanced along the road of patriotism with greatest national pride and self-esteem which no other nations in the world could ever have in the history spanning more than half a century thanks to the glorious motherland glorified by you. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We will make a tangible contribution to the prosperity and development of the country with confidence in the bright future of the country, resolutely smash the Japanese reactionaries' all moves for suppression and conspiratorial plots to separate the Koreans in Japan from the fold of the DPRK with the unbreakable will and the might of the single-minded unity and thus firmly defend Chongryon.

Japanese Government's Inhumane Action under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Tokyo, September 8 (KNS-KCNA) -- Nam Sung U, vice-chairman of the Central Standing Committee of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon), called an emergency press conference in Tokyo on September 7 in protest against the Japanese government's inhumane action. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were reporters of Chongryon and Japanese media persons. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Nam Sung U referred to the fact that a written request was sent by Chongryon to the Japanese government on September 6 to allow a portcall of a DPRK ship on Japan to send aid materials to the flood-stricken compatriots, but it turned down the request. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He branded this attitude on the part of the Japanese government as a senseless and inhumane action. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Expressing the determination to continue urging the Japanese government to meet the above-said request in the future, too, he strongly demanded the Japanese government lift the sanctions against the DPRK and ensure the free visits of Koreans in Japan to their homeland.

Kim Jong Il recibe mensaje de felicitacion de cuadros chinos
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 8 de septiembre (ATCC) -- El Dirigente Kim Jong Il, Secretario General del Partido del Trabajo de Corea y Presidente del Comite de Defensa Nacional de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea (RPDC), junto con Kim Yong Nam, presidente del Presidium de la Asamblea Popular Suprema, y Kim Yong Il, primer ministro del Consejo de Ministros, recibio un mensaje de felicitacion que les enviaran el dia 8 Hu Jintao, Secretario General del Comite Central del Partido Comunista de China (PCCh) y Presidente de la Republica Popular China (RPCh) y de la Comision Militar Central de la RPCh, Wu Bangguo, presidente del Comite Permanente de la Asamblea Popular Nacional de la RPCh, y Wen Jiabao, primer ministro del Consejo de Estado de la RPCh, con motivo del 59o aniversario de la fundacion de la RPDC. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La fundacion de la RPDC escribio una nueva pagina en que el pueblo coreano construye el Estado socialista siendo el dueno del pais, comienza el mensaje y prosigue: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Bajo la direccion del Presidente Kim Il Sung, el Secretario General Kim Jong Il y del PTC, el pueblo coreano logro grandes exitos en el cumplimiento de la causa de construccion del socialismo dando pruebas de su espiritu de apoyo en las propias fuerzas y lucha tenaz. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Deseamos de todo corazon que el pueblo coreano alcance en lo adelante tambien incesantes y nuevos exitos en todas sus labores. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Avanzaremos junto con la epoca y reforzaremos la cooperacion con la parte coreana para atribuir mas vigorosidad a la tradicional amistad China-Corea y esperamos que de esa manera hagamos un nuevo aporte a dar mayor felicidad a los pueblos de los dos paises y fomentar la paz y la estabilidad de la region.

Acto central por el 59o aniversario de la fundacion de la RPDC
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 8 de septiembre (ATCC) -- Tuvo lugar este sabado en la Casa Cultural 25 de Abril el acto central por el 59o aniversario de la fundacion de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
